The paper focuses on facial image compression, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves learning-based techniques (cs.MM) and optimization of parameters (cs.IT). The use of a hybrid semantic fidelity metric and Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
